 trying to keep his life intact despite health concerns; Jackie, a young African-American woman diligently attending school after work; and Cindy, whose matter-of-fact attitude helps Deepak adapt to his job and his new life. How May I Help You? is an incisive take on life in the United States and a reminder that the stories of low-wage employees can bring candor and humanity to debates about work, race, and immigration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aForeign workerszUnited States. 0aImmigrantszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aImmigrantszUnited StatesxEconomic conditions. 0aWorking poorzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Classes & Economic Disparity.2bisacsh  aafrican american.  aamerican history.  ablack americans.  acareer.  acareers.  aco workers.  acolleagues.  acommunity.  aculture.  aelectronics.  aemotional.  aimmigrant story.  aimmigrant.  aimmigration.  aindian culture.  aindian immigrant.  ajobs.  alow wage.  aminimum wage.  amotivational.  anew life.  arace issues.  arace.  aracism.  aracist.  aretail.  asmall town.  astarting over.  atrue story.  aunited states.  avirginia.  aworkplace issues.  aworkplace.1 aSingh, Holly Donahue, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106675540 cprintz978052029331140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520966475423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520966475/original  a978-3-11-066755-4  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles